.TH "pcm_trigger" 9 "pcm_trigger" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pcm_trigger \- implements trigger callback function for PCM middle layer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pcm_trigger
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ","
.BI "int cmd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "substream" 12
substream pointer
.IP "cmd" 12
action to perform
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is called when the PCM is started, stopped or paused. The action will be
specified in the second argument, SNDRV_PCM_TRIGGER_XXX

Returns 0 on success or error code otherwise.
